%20think%20of%20the%20Guard%20is%20as%20a%20classic%20citizen-soldier%2C%26quot%3B%20Rachel%20VanLandingham%2C%20a%20national%20security%20expert%20and%20professor%20at%20Southwestern%20Law%20School%2C%20said.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.army.mil%2Farticle%2F272427%2Fnational_guard_celebrates_387_years_of_being_always_ready_always_there%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThose%20state%20militias%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20transformed%20over%20250%20years%20into%20individual%20state%20National%20Guards%2C%20with%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FNews-Stories%2FArticle%2FArticle%2F3671244%2Fnational-guard-bureau-leaders-say-taking-care-of-guardsmen-is-key-to-meeting-mi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E430%2C000%20members%3C%2Fa%3E%20collectively%20across%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Guard%20is%20made%20up%20of%20regular%20community%20members%20such%20as%20teachers%2C%20bankers%2C%20social%20workers%2C%20and%20so%20on%20who%20can%20be%20called%20up%20to%20respond%20to%20emergencies%20at%20the%20discretion%20of%20their%20state%20governors.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20there's%20a%20need%2C%20they're%20gonna%20put%20on%20a%20uniform%2C%26quot%3B%20VanLandingham%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20they%20specifically%20belong%20to%20the%20state.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20generally%20two%20categories%20of%20people%20who%20join%20the%20National%20Guard%2C%20said%20Katherine%20Kuzminski%2C%20who%20oversees%20the%20Center%20for%20a%20New%20American%20Security's%20military%2C%20veterans%2C%20and%20society%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20National%20Guard%20troops%20are%20either%20pursuing%20a%20civilian%20career%20but%20still%20want%20to%20serve%20or%20were%20once%20on%20active%20duty%20but%20are%20now%20part-timers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20reserves%20and%20active%20forces%2C%20National%20Guard%20troops%20go%20through%20basic%20training%20with%20follow-on%20specialized%20job%20training.%20They%20hold%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnationalguard.com%2Fcareers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Especific%20military%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20can%20include%20anything%20from%20truck%20mechanic%20or%20pilot%20to%20infantryman%20or%20admin%20specialist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20active%20troops%20are%20assigned%20to%20military%20bases%20that%20are%20usually%20far%20removed%20from%20heavily%20populated%20areas%2C%20leading%20to%20less%20overlap%20with%20civilians%2C%20most%20Americans%20rarely%20engage%20with%20active%20troops%2C%20and%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20know%20someone%20who's%20in%20the%20Guard%20or%20the%20Reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22North%20Carolina%20National%20Guardsmen%20assigned%20to%20the%20130th%20Maneuver%20Enhancement%20Brigade%20clear%20debris%20at%20Lake%20Lure%2C%20N.C.%2C%20Oct.%208th%2C%202024%20as%20part%20of%20Hurricane%20Helene%20relief%20efforts.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a66c237bb3f854015c3b31%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENorth%20Carolina%20National%20Guardsmen%20assigned%20to%20the%20130th%20Maneuver%20Enhancement%20Brigade%20clear%20debris%20at%20Lake%20Lure%2C%20N.C.%2C%20Oct.%208th%2C%202024%20as%20part%20of%20Hurricane%20Helene%20relief%20efforts.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Army%20National%20Guard%20photo%20by%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Hannah%20Tarkelly%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20to%20the%20Guard%2C%20reserve%20forces%20are%20the%20part%20time%20equivalent%20of%20the%20active-duty%20force.%20Many%20reservists%20are%20also%20former%20full-time%20troops%20who%20were%20once%20on%20active%20duty.%20Reservists%20frequently%20belong%20to%20units%20based%20outside%20their%20home%20states%2C%20meaning%20they%20might%20travel%20monthly%20to%20%26quot%3Bdrill%2C%26quot%3B%20performing%20routine%20duties%20to%20stay%20fresh%20in%20uniform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Guard%20troops%20and%20reservists%20are%20usually%20obligated%20to%20serve%20one%20weekend%20a%20month%20in%20uniform%20and%20then%20at%20least%20two%20consecutive%20weeks%20yearly%20to%20maintain%20military%20skillsets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EActive-duty%20service%20members%20enlist%20for%20a%20specific%20number%20of%20years%2C%20with%20options%20to%20extend.%20They%20live%20on%20or%20near%20the%20military%20base%20to%20which%20they%20are%20assigned.%20Most%20active%20service%20members%20work%20normal%20workdays%20but%20are%20expected%20to%20undergo%20long%20training%20exercises%2C%20perform%20overnight%20duties%2C%20and%20are%20often%20on%20call%2024%2F7.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22311ad6f8-37e0-4213-9acc-792a1e299808%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20do%20they%20answer%20to%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20differences%20between%20Guard%2C%20reserve%2C%20and%20active-duty%20forces%20are%20in%20their%20chains%20of%20command%20and%20legal%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20the%20chain%20of%20command%20for%20all%20reservists%20and%20active%20troops%20is%20entirely%20through%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%2C%20up%20to%20the%20service%20secretaries%20and%20the%20president.%20States%20have%20no%20control%20over%20reserve%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20the%20armed%20services%20under%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%20has%20its%20own%20reserve%20component%2C%20but%20only%20the%20Army%20and%20Air%20Force%20have%20National%20Guards.%20States%20have%20not%20historically%20needed%20naval%20forces%2C%20Kuzminski%20said%2C%20so%20the%20Department%20of%20the%20Navy%20(which%20includes%20the%20Marine%20Corps)%20doesn't%20have%20a%20National%20Guard%20component.%20Right%20now%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbreakingdefense.com%2F2024%2F11%2Fcould-trump-establish-a-space-national-guard-officials-and-experts-say-its-likely%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethere%20isn't%20a%20Space%20Force%20National%20Guard%3C%2Fa%3E%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReservists%20also%20have%20