s%2C%20including%20Eli%20Sharabi%2C%20Or%20Levy%2C%20and%20Ohad%20Ben%20Ami%2C%20were%20returned%20after%20nearly%20500%20days%2C%20but%20with%20Israel%20condemning%20Hamas%20for%20their%20severe%20condition.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20WORLD%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fmonsters-israel-releases-pictures-of-pale-and-malnourished-hostages-after-hamas-freed-them%2Farticleshow%2F118084595.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tips%20for%20handling%20conflicts%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20according%20to%20experts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22two%20people%20fighting%20at%20a%20desk%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67082fdd3f2165d716e00526%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223449%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENavigating%20conflicts%20at%20work%20can%20be%20awkward%2C%20but%20there%20are%20steps%20you%20can%20take%20to%20try%20to%20defuse%20these%20difficult%20situations.%3Cp%3EYana%20Iskayeva%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20never%20pleasant%2C%20but%20it%20happens%20sometimes%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-handle-conflict-2017-3%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYou%20find%20yourself%20in%20conflict%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20someone%20at%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHow%20do%20you%20best%20address%20it%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20shared%20with%20BI%20their%20tips%20for%20tactfully%20handling%20disagreements%20with%20coworkers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20uncomfortable%20situation%3A%20having%20a%20conflict%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20you%20handle%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20not%20always%20an%20easy%20solution%2C%20but%20there%20are%20steps%20you%20can%20take%20to%20try%20to%20defuse%20difficult%20situations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20emotions%20are%20running%20high%2C%20remember%20to%20%26quot%3Btake%20a%20deep%20breath%20and%20pause%20for%20a%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Lisa%20Richey%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famericanetiquette.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20American%20Academy%20of%20Etiquette%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20many%20of%20us%20are%20so%20quick%20to%20react%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BTake%20time%20to%20understand%20why%20the%20other%20person%20may%20be%20bringing%20up%20a%20particular%20issue.%20The%20only%20thing%20that%20we%20can%20control%20is%20the%20way%20we%20react%20to%20it%20in%20the%20moment.%20You%20have%20to%20be%20fully%20responsible%20for%20yourself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20also%20be%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20keep%20your%20discussions%20out%20of%20earshot%20or%20view%20of%20people%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAddress%20it%20later%2C%20one-on-one%20with%20the%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20Richey%20said.%20%26quot%3BDo%20not%20get%20into%20these%20heated%20conversations%20and%20battles%20within%20the%20conference%20room%20as%20a%20group.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArden%20Clise%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcliseetiquette.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClise%20Etiquette%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20emphasized%20having%20a%20%26quot%3Bcalm%2C%20respectful%20conversation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsider%20sticking%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Fhow-to-be-vulnerable%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BI%26quot%3B%20statements%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20express%20your%20perspective%20or%20feelings%20about%20something%2C%20versus%20%26quot%3Byou%26quot%3B%20statements%2C%20which%20can%20carry%20an%20accusatory%20or%20combative%20intonation%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20you're%20at%20fault%20for%20something%2C%20apologize.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Eliot%2C%20organizational%20psychology%20professor%20at%20Texas%20A%26amp%3BM%20University%2C%20writes%20in%20his%20forthcoming%20book%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theconflictdocs.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BHow%20to%20Get%20Along%20With%20Anyone%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20many%20people%20fall%20into%20one%20of%20five%20personality%20styles%20regarding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-manage-conflict-in-a-relationship-according-to-experts-2018-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20they%20behave%20in%20conflicts.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20take%20a%20few%20minutes%20to%20really%20understand%20yourself%2C%20then%20you're%20equipped%20to%20know%20what%20types%20of%20office%20conflict%20you'll%20naturally%20be%20good%20at%20and%20what%20you'll%20struggle%20at%2C%20and%20that's%20half%20the%20battle%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20other%20half%20of%20the%20battle%20is%20take%20some%20time%20to%20figure%20out%20the%20style%20of%20the%20people%20you're%20working%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20conflict%2C%20Eliot%20suggests%20considering%20the%20other%20person's%20conflict%20style%20and%20what%20it%20is%20they're%20looking%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20to%20agree%2C%20we%20don't%20have%20to%20solve%20the%20problem%2C%20we%20don't%20even%20have%20to%20have%20the%20same%20opinions%20on%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20I%20know%20one%20or%20two%20things%20they're%20looking%20for%2C%20I%20can%20brainstorm%20a%20way%20to%20give%20them%20one%20of%20those%20things%20so%20that%20we%20can%20diffuse%20emotion.%20Once%20the%20emotion%20is%20diffused%2C%20then%20you%20can%20get%20back%20to%20having%20a%20more%20rational%20conversation%20with%20one%20another.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Factive-listening%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPracticing%20active%20listening%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20disagreement%20can%20help%20%26quot%3Bbring%20people%20together%20even%20if%20we%20disagree%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Eliot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20all%20have%20a%20need%20to%20feel%20heard%20and%20feel%20understood%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BMake%20sure%20you're%20understanding%20what%20they're%20saying%20and%20then%20feed%20some%20of%20that%20back%20a%20little%20bit.%20That's%20an%20active%20way%20to%20let%20them%20know%2C%20'This%20person%20really%20is%20listening%20to%20me.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20an%20argument%20is%20getting%20heated%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femt-dad-shares-how-stay-calm-during-stressful-situations-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etry%20setting%20a%20calmer%20tone%20yourself%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20other%20person%20may%20follow%2C%20Eliot%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimply%20slowing%20down%20the%20pace%20of%20your%20discussion%20can%20also%20help%20defuse%20tensions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20taking%20a%20second%20to%20slow%20down%20in%20the%20way%20you%20talk%2C%20that%20will%20slow%20down%20an%20interaction%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Eliot.%20%26quot%3BIn%20basketball%2C%20we%20take%20a%2030-second%20timeout%20with%20our%20kids%2C%20and%20it%20brings%20emotions%20down.%20If%20what%20you%20are%20going%20to%20say%20would%20normally%20take%20you%20two%20seconds%2C%20and%20you%20take%2015%20seconds%20instead%20of%20two%2C%20then%20you're%20infusing%20the%20spirit%20of%20a%20timeout%20into%20a%20conversation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20sometimes%2C%20there's%20no%20satisfactory%20win-win%20or%20compromise%20to%20a%20conflict%20at%20work.%20In%20those%20cases%2C%20sometimes%20you%20just%20have%20to%20pick%20your%20battles.%20Because%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20they'll%20still%20be%20your%20coworkers%20tomorrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20if%20being%20the%20bigger%20person%20means%20you%20have%20to%20lose%20the%20battle%20(but%20hopefully%20win%20the%20war%20of%20working%20together%20harmoniously%20longterm)%2C%20%26quot%3Bjust%20remember%20that%20we%20are%20working%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Clise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20maintain%20good%20relationships%20with%20the%20people%20we%20are%20working%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-handle-conflicts-disagreements-with-coworkers-at-work-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739094541000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a67c306630eb10385c00de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-handle-conflicts-disagreements-with-coworkers-at-work-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Navigating%20conflicts%20at%20work%20can%20be%20awkward%20or%20stressful%2C%20but%20there%20are%20steps%20you%20can%20take%20to%20try%20to%20defuse%20difficult%20situations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sjackson%40insider.com%20(Sarah%20Jackson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-handle-conflicts-disagreements-with-coworkers-at-work-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20big%20Delhi%20win%2C%20Parvesh%20Verma%20vows%20to%20fulfil%20father%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98unfinished%20works%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739094490000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-118087613%2Cimgsize-25432.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fafter-big-delhi-win-bjps-parvesh-verma-pays-tribute-to-father-vows-to-fulfil-his-unfinished-works%2Farticleshow%2F118087621.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22BJP%20leader%20Parvesh%20Verma%20paid%20tributes%20to%20his%20father's%20memorial%2C%20emphasizing%20his%20commitm