2fff9a381b8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMalena%20DeMartini%20doesn't%20want%20to%20say%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-mandate-wfh-breaking-employer-boss-worker-trust-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn-to-office%20mandates%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20good%20for%20business%20because%20there's%20nothing%20good%20about%20the%20prospect%20of%20dogs%20suffering.%20But%20as%20a%20dog%20trainer%20who%20specializes%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fprevent-separation-anxiety-in-dogs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseparation%20anxiety%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she's%20recently%20been%20inundated%20with%20clients.%20After%20years%20of%20having%20their%20owners%20around%20all%20day%2C%20many%20pets%20aren't%20accustomed%20to%20being%20alone%20anymore%20%E2%80%94%20some%20have%20never%20spent%20any%20time%20solo%20at%20all.%20So%20when%20the%20boss%20says%20it's%20time%20to%20pack%20it%20in%20on%20remote%20work%2C%20many%20people%20are%20caught%20flat-footed%2C%20and%20their%20animals%20are%20paying%20the%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20won't%20sugarcoat%20it.%20It's%20much%20harder%20if%20people%20haven't%20prepared%20in%20advance%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BKeep%20your%20little%20furry%20friend%20in%20mind%20because%20it's%20a%20drastic%20transition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20many%20pet%20owners%20have%20slept%20on%20the%20preparedness%20front.%20Their%20employers%20are%20demanding%20they%20come%20back%20to%20the%20office%2C%20and%20even%20the%20most%20understanding%20of%20managers%20may%20not%20be%20super%20open%20to%20%26quot%3Bmy%20dog%20will%20be%20sad%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20valid%20excuse%20for%20a%20permanent%20work-from-home%20exception.%20This%20has%20left%20people%20to%20scramble%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20to%20do%20with%20their%20pets%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20not%20accustomed%20to%20spending%20long%20stretches%20of%20time%20by%20themselves.%20Concerned%20owners%20are%20signing%20their%20dogs%20up%20for%20day%20care%2C%20rushing%20to%20find%20walkers%20and%20sitters%2C%20and%20buying%20treat-dispensing%20video%20cameras%20they%20hope%20will%20calm%20their%20pets'%20nerves%20(and%20their%20own).%20For%20those%20who%20have%20yet%20to%20get%20an%20RTO%20order%2C%20DeMartini%20recommends%20acting%20like%20one%20is%20coming%20anyway.%20Teach%20your%20dog%20to%20be%20by%20itself%20now%2C%20before%20you're%20panicked%20about%20whether%20your%20little%20guy%20will%20destroy%20your%20couch%20as%20retribution%20for%20your%209-to-5.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20pet%20conundrum%20has%20become%20a%20familiar%20story%3A%20Lonely%20people%20stuck%20at%20home%20in%202020%20decided%20it%20was%20an%20opportune%20time%20to%20get%20a%20new%20dog%20or%20cat%2C%20figuring%20that%20they%20finally%20had%20time%20to%20dedicate%20to%20such%20an%20endeavor.%20In%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aspcapro.org%2Fresource%2Fnew-aspca-survey-vast-majority-dogs-and-cats-acquired-during-pandemic-still-their-homes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Society%20for%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Cruelty%20to%20Animals%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20US%20residents%2C%20one%20in%20five%20respondents%20said%20their%20household%20got%20a%20cat%20or%20dog%20between%20March%202020%20and%20May%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20more%20people%20who%20wanted%20to%20foster%20or%20adopt%20than%20we%20had%20pets%20in%20the%20shelters%2C%20which%20was%20incredible%20to%20see%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tori%20Fugate%2C%20the%20director%20of%20communications%20for%20Shelter%20Animals%20Count%2C%20a%20national%20database%20for%20animal%20rescues%20and%20shelters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdrienne%20Preuss%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20Animal%20Loving%20Care%2C%20a%20dog%20day%20care%20and%20boarding%20facility%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20New%20York%2C%20said%20that%20while%20the%20pandemic%20brought%20about%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20surge%26quot%3B%20in%20people%20getting%20pets%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20new%20owners%20made%20%26quot%3Bspur-of-the-moment%20decisions%26quot%3B%20and%20weren't%20prepared%20for%20what%20came%20next.%20Her%20business%20started%20offering%20remote%20dog%20training%20and%20sending%20instructional%20videos%20to%20clients%20who%20were%20struggling%20with%20their%20new%20wards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20puppies%20that%20came%20in%20during%20that%20time%20with%20behavioral%20issues%20for%20a%20number%20of%20reasons.%20The%20biggest%20reason%20was%20that%20people%20were%20not%20leaving%20them%20at%20any%20period%20of%20time%2C%20so%20they%20were%20either%20with%20the%20owners%20constantly%20at%20home%20or%20with%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20period%20of%20time%20where%20they%20were%20not%20with%20humans%2C%20and%20that's%20not%20ideal%20for%20setting%20up%20a%20dog%20to%20feel%20confident%20being%20by%20themselves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20as%20the%20pandemic%20eased%20and%20people%20returned%20to%20their%20normal%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20going%20out%20to%20dinner%2C%20taking%20vacations%2C%20and%20easing%20their%20way%20back%20into%20the%20office%20%E2%80%94%20they%20were%20confronted%20with%20a%20crop%20of%20pets%20who%20had%20no%20idea%20how%20to%20make%20do%20on%20their%20own.%20As%20the%20return-to-office%20push%20has%20continued%2C%20more%20and%20more%20pet%20owners%20are%20finding%20themselves%20in%20a%20pickle.%20Serveral%20major%20companies%20are%20trying%20to%20strong-arm%20their%20workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eback%20into%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20AT%26amp%3BT%2C%20Citigroup%2C%20and%20Dell%20are%20telling%20employees%20to%20come%20in%20full%20time%2C%20and%20others%2C%20including%20Apple%20and%20Starbucks%2C%20are%20requiring%20part-time%20in-office%20work.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-federal-return-to-office-mandate-workers-living-far-guidance-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20ordered%20federal%20agencies%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20people%20back%20into%20the%20office%2C%20too.%20In%20addition%20to%20all%20the%20other%20disruptions%20of%20the%20RTO%20orders%2C%20pet%20owners%20are%20concerned%20their%20dogs%20have%20separation%20anxiety%2C%20and%20even%20if%20he%20doesn't%2C%20Fido%20may%20not%20be%20jazzed%20about%20staying%20home%20alone%20%E2%80%94%20or%20able%20to%20do%20so%20responsibly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDogs%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20dog%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kate%20Meghji%2C%20the%20chief%20operating%20officer%20of%20the%20Humane%20Rescue%20Alliance%2C%20an%20animal-service%20provider%20based%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacob%20Hensley%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20District%20Dogs%2C%20a%20dog%20day%20care%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20said%20he%20sees%20an%20influx%20of%20new%20clients%20whenever%20a%20big%20return-to-office%20mandate%20hits%20the%20area.%20This%20year%20already%2C%20he%20saw%20a%20jump%20in%20account%20creations%20and%20new%20reservations%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-rto-issues-space-security-productivity-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20started%20requiring%20people%20to%20come%20in%20five%20days%20a%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January%2C%20and%20he's%20seeing%20even%20more%20now%20as%20federal%20workers%20are%20being%20told%20to%20show%20up%20in%20person.%20He's%20also%20getting%20clients%20as%20people%20move%20to%20the%20area%20because%20of%20RTO%20asks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhenever%20we%20see%20a%20new%20customer%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20conversations%20talk%20about%26quot%3B%20a%20return%20to%20the%20office%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20District%20Dogs%20opened%20a%20location%20at%20Amazon's%20HQ2%20campus%20in%20Arlington%2C%20Virginia%2C%20to%20help%20accommodate%20(and%20pick%20up%20business%20from)%20employees%20going%20into%20the%20office.%20Hensley%20is%20now%20in%20discussions%20with%20a%20large%20employer%20in%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20area%20to%20put%20together%20some%20sort%20of%20dog%20day%20care%20benefit%20for%20employees%20coming%20back%20to%20the%20office.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20living%20in%20a%20fur%20baby%20age%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20don't%20have%20to%20do%20a%20deep%20dive%20into%20Reddit%20to%20find%20examples%20of%20workers%20fretting%20about%20what%20to%20do%20with%20their%20beloved%20pets%20while%20they%20spend%20the%20day%20putting%20in%20their%20time%20with%20The%20Man.%20%26quot%3BAnyone%20else%20concerned%20about%20what%20they'll%20do%20with%20their%20pets%20if%20they're%20gone%2010%20or%20more%20hours%20a%20day%20commuting%20with%20RTO%3F%26quot%3B%20one%20Redditor%20wrote%20in%20January%20on%20a%20forum%20for%20federal%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%2C%20exactly%2C%20is%20one%20to%20do%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESending%20your%20dog%20to%20day%20care%20is%20a%20decent%20option%20for%20workers%2C%20but%20it%20has%20its%20limitations.%20For%20one%20thing%2C%20it's%20expensive.%20District%20Dogs%20in%20Alexandria%2C%20for%20example%2C%20charges%20%2450%20a%20day%2C%20as%20does%20Animal%20Loving%20Care%2C%20though%20they%20give%20discounts%20for%20packages.%20For%20many%20people%2C%20sending%20a%20dog%20to%20day%20care%20five%20days%20a%20week%20isn't%20feasible%2C%20not%20only%20because%20of%20costs%20but%20also%20because%20the%20dog%20may%20not%20want%20to%20be%20there.%20If%20the%20pet%20hasn't%20been%20socialized%20correctly%2C%20it%20might%20not%20take%20well%20to%20day%20care%2C%20and%20even%20if%20it%20has%2C%20older%20dogs%20tend%20to%20age%20out%20of%20day%20care%20enjoyment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeMartini%20said%20we're%20%26quot%3Bonly%20limited%20by%20our%20creativity%26quot%3B%20with%20finding%20people%20who%20can%20watch%20dogs%20at%20little%20or%20no%20cost.%20She%20suggested%20reaching%20out%20to%20retirement%20communities%20to%20see%20whether%20they%20might%20benefit%20from%20a%20furry%20friend%20from%20time%20to%20time%20or%20calling%20up%20a%20family%20member%2C%20friend%2C%20or%20neighbor%20who%20has%20more%20spare%20time.%20There%20are%20always%20dog%20walkers%2C%20but%20again%2C%20that%20can%20get%20expensive%2C%20and%20your%20walker%20probably%20isn't%20going%20to%20spend%20eight%20hours%20with%20your%20pet.%20You%20can%20also%20ask%20about%20bringing%20your%20dog%20to%20work%2C%20but%20your%20manager%20and%20your%20coworkers%20may%20not%20be%20open%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20worst-case%20scenario%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20that%20someone%20winds%20up%20renouncing%20their%20pet%20because%20they%20feel%20they%20can't%20make%20it%20work.%20Shelter%20Animals%20Count%2C%20which%20tracks%20animal%20rescues%20and%20shelters%20across%20the%20US%2C%20found%20that%205.8%20million%20pets%20were%20taken%20in%20by%20shelters%20and%20rescues%20in%202024%2C%20which%20is%20still%20below%20the%20prepandemic%20level%20but%20a%20jump%20from%20the%20pandemic%20low%20of%205.3%20million%20in%202020.%20When%20pets%20do%20land%20in%20a%20shelter%2C%20it's%20now%20taking%20them%20longer%20to%20get%20adopted%20than%20in%202020%20when%20they%20were%20getting%20scooped%20up%2C%20which%20is%20leaving%20shelters%20overwhelmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFugate%20said%20that%20it's%20not%20clear%20whether%20RTO%20has%20been%20a%20major%20driver%20of%20pet%20returns.%20It's%20often%20economic%20factors%20(vet%20bills%20and%20food%20are%20expensive)%20or%20because%20of%20housing%20problems%20%E2%80%94%20many%20places%20don't%20accept%20pets.%20Preuss%20from%20Animal%20Loving%20Care%20said%20that%20she%20saw%20an%20%26quot%3Bunprecedented%20level%26quot%3B%20of%20people%20giving%20away%20pets%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic%20but%20that%20things%20had%20normalized%20since%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20those%20who%20keep%20their%20dogs%20now%20may%20be%20hesitant%20about%20adopting%20again%20if%20they%20have%20a%20negative%20experience.%20Meghji%20said%20that%20people%20generally%20seem%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20committed%26quot%3B%20to%20working%20with%20their%20pets%20and%20modifying%20their%20lifestyles%2C%20even%20amid%20behavioral%20challenges%2C%20but%20she%20worries%20about%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20that%20means%20the%20next%20time%20they're%20thinking%20about%20getting%20a%20dog.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20how%20unprepared%20your%20pandemic%20pup%20may%20be%2C%20every%20animal%20behavior%20expert%20and%20day%20care%20owner%20I%20spoke%20with%20for%20this%20story%20said%20it's%20critical%20for%20a%20pet%20to%20be%20able%20to%20be%20by%20itself%20for%20at%20least%20some%20chunks%20of%20time.%20It%20might%20take%20some%20practice%20and%20effort%20(or%20a%20lot)%20and%20some%20development%20of%20a%20routine%2C%20but%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20it's%20good%20for%20a%20dog%20to%20be%20able%20to%20self-soothe%20and%20have%20some%20me%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20worried%20about%20your%20pet%20being%20at%20home%20alone%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20figure%20out%20whether%20they're%20actually%20suffering%20from%20separation%20anxiety%2C%20which%20is%20a%20clinically%20diagnosed%20condition%2C%20or%20the%20problem%20is%20something%20else.%20People%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20attribute%20%3Cem%3Eeverything%20%3C%2Fem%3Etheir%20animal%20does%20that%20they%20don't%20like%20to%20anxiety%2C%20even%20when%20that%20may%20not%20be%20the%20root%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeparation%20anxiety%20can%20manifest%20in%20various%20ways.%20Some%20dogs%20bark%20or%20howl%20endlessly.%20Some%20try%20to%20escape.%20Some%20destroy%20things.%20Others%20will%20urinate%20or%20defecate%20out%20of%20worry.%20Katherine%20Houpt%2C%20a%20professor%20emeritus%20of%20animal%20behavioral%20medicine%20at%20Cornell%20University%20College%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine%2C%20said%20the%20best%20thing%20pet%20owners%20can%20do%20is%20to%20get%20a%20camera%20so%20they%20can%20see%20how%20their%20dog%20is%20reacting%20when%20they%20leave.%20That%20may%20also%20help%20them%20figure%20out%20whether%20what's%20happening%20is%20even%20separation%20anxiety%20%E2%80%94%20your%20dog%20might%20tear%20up%20your%20apartment%20because%20it's%20sad%20you're%20gone%2C%20or%20it%20might%20do%20it%20because%20it's%20bored%20and%20destruction%20is%20fun.%20Houpt%20worked%20with%20one%20dog%20whose%20owners%20thought%20he%20had%20separation%20anxiety%2C%20but%20video%20revealed%20he%20was%20playing%20%E2%80%94%20he%20took%20a%20couch%20cushion%2C%20tore%20it%20apart%2C%20rolled%20around%20in%20it%2C%20and%20at%20one%20point%20grabbed%20a%20toilet%20bowl%20brush%20to%20seemingly%20stir%20the%20escaped%20couch%20feathers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20tactics%20people%20can%20deploy%20to%20ease%20their%20dog's%20stress%20if%20they%20do%20indeed%20have%20separation%20anxiety.%20Talking%20to%20a%20dog%20via%20video%20camera%20or%20leaving%20on%20videos%20tailored%20to%20dogs%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20do%20much%2C%20Houpt%20said.%20Getting%20your%20dog%20a%20friend%20might%20help%2C%20but%20the%20animals%20might%20fight%2C%20or%20you%20might%20just%20wind%20up%20with%20two%20anxious%20pets.%20It%20may%20also%20help%20to%20give%20the%20dog%20a%20special%20treat%20it%20takes%20a%20long%20time%20to%20eat%20when%20you%20leave%2C%20though%20if%20it%20really%20has%20separation%20anxiety%2C%20it%20might%20not%20eat%20while%20you're%20gone.%20And%20there%20are%20always%20medications%20%E2%80%94%20fluoxetine%20(Reconcile)%20and%20clomipramine%20(Clomicalm)%20are%20Food%20and%20Drug%20Administration-approved%20for%20separation%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20dog%20is%20good%20for%20six%20months%2C%20I'd%20treat%20him%20for%20another%20six%20months%20and%20then%20try%20weaning%20him%20off%2C%20and%20it%20may%20be%20fine%2C%26quot%3B%20Houpt%20said%20of%20using%20the%20drugs.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20learned%20that%20when%20you%20leave%2C%20the%20world%20doesn't%20come%20to%20an%20end%20and%20that%20you%20always%20come%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20suspect%20your%20pet%20has%20separation%20anxiety%2C%20you%20may%20want%20to%20get%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-pet-insurance-worth-it-cost-scams-premiums-preexisting-conditions-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epet%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20wait%20on%20a%20diagnosis%20if%20you%20can%20so%20the%20insurance%20will%20cover%20it%20and%20it%20won't%20be%20determined%20to%20be%20a%20preexisting%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20there%20are%20other%20steps%20between%20quitting%20your%20job%20so%20your%20dog%20isn't%20alone%20and%20medicating%20your%20dog%20so%20it%20can%20make%20it%20through%20the%20day.%20A%20lot%20of%20it%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20practicing%20alone%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTeaching%20the%20dog%20to%20stay%2C%20as%20simple%20as%20it%20sounds%20%E2%80%94%20it%20is%20really%20curative%20because%20many%20of%20these%20dogs%20have%20never%20had%20to%20inhibit%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20Houpt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeMartini%20recommends%20exposing%20dogs%20to%20small%20amounts%20of%20alone%20time%20so%20they%20get%20used%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20people%20will%20go%20away%20and%20come%20back.%20First%2C%20one%20minute%2C%20then%20three%2C%20then%20five%2C%20and%20so%20on%2C%20until%2C%20eventually%2C%20you%20can%20leave%20for%20varying%20lengths%20of%20time%2C%20though%20progress%20may%20not%20be%20linear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20it%20sounds%20like%2C%20'Wow%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20take%20five%20years%20to%20get%20my%20dog%20to%20be%20left%20alone%2C'%20it's%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20like%20compounding%20interest%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20similar%20to%20exposure%20therapy%20that%20we've%20used%20with%20humans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreuss%20from%20Animal%20Loving%20Care%20also%20pressed%20the%20importance%20of%20crate%20training%2C%20even%20if%20you%20think%20your%20dog%20doesn't%20need%20it.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20your%20dog%20is%20great%20out%20of%20the%20crate%2C%20it's%20a%20really%20essential%20and%20useful%20resource%20to%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20dogs%20that%20come%20in%20to%20us%20who've%20never%20seen%20a%20crate%20in%20their%20life%2C%20so%20they%20can't%20even%20be%20separated%20in%20the%20environment%20to%20eat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20and%20when%20you%20do%20wind%20up%20going%20to%20work%20and%20leaving%20your%20dog%20behind%2C%20when%20you%20get%20home%2C%20don't%20make%20a%20big%20deal%20about%20it.%20If%20you%20do%20an%20exaggerated%2C%20enthusiastic%20greeting%20and%20play%20and%20get%20the%20dog%20all%20excited%2C%20it'll%20turn%20that%20into%20the%20highlight%20of%20its%20day%20%E2%80%94%20and%20make%20the%20time%20when%20you're%20gone%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20aside%20here%2C%20cats%20are%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20different%20story.%20If%20a%20cat%20has%20separation%20anxiety%2C%20it%20might%20go%20unnoticed%2C%20DeMartini%20said%2C%20because%20their%20outward%20behavior%2C%20something%20like%20hiding%20away%20or%20drooling%2C%20isn't%20really%20impactful%20on%20their%20owner.%20Houpt%20said%20she'd%20never%20seen%20a%20clinical%20case%20of%20a%20cat%20with%20separation%20anxiety%2C%20though%20people%20say%20they%20exist.%20But%20she%20noted%20they're%20generally%20a%20more%20solitary%20species%20and%20don't%20mind%20being%20alone%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20time.%20(If%20you%20have%20a%20cat%2C%20you%20probably%20know%20this.)%20She%20also%20recommended%20making%20sure%20the%20animal%20doesn't%20have%20some%20sort%20of%20underlying%20medical%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYes%2C%20the%20cat%20is%20pulling%20its%20fur%20out%2C%20but%20it%20probably%20has%20a%20dermatological%20problem%2C%20not%20a%20psychological%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20set%20up%20your%20camera%20and%20see%20if%20the%20cat%20is%20spending%20four%20hours%20glued%20to%20the%20front%20door.%20Then%20maybe%20you%20do%20have%20a%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-hybrid-jobs-rto-jpmorgan-amazon-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epush%20and%20pull%20between%20employers%20and%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20work%20back%20into%20the%20office%20is%20not%20going%20away.%20As%20companies%20feel%20they%20have%20more%20leverage%2C%20many%20will%20do%20what%20they%20can%20to%20get%20workers%20back%20in.%20And%20workers%20who%20have%20become%20accustomed%20to%20the%20flexibility%20of%20remote%20and%20hybrid%20arrangements%20will%20continue%20to%20resist.%20Pets%20are%20unwittingly%20caught%20up%20in%20the%20battle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20if%20you%20think%20your%20boss%20will%20be%20cool%20with%20you%20working%20from%20home%20forever%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20get%20around%20to%20teaching%20your%20dog%20to%20exist%20comfortably%20without%20you%20around%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later.%20Employers%20are%20sure%20to%20keep%20pushing%20on%20RTO%2C%20and%20regardless%2C%20you%20probably%20should%20be%20able%20to%20go%20to%20the%20grocery%20store%20or%20happy%20hour%20without%20your%20pup%20having%20a%20meltdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpets-l